explanation: The solution utilizes a sorted list of ranges to efficiently track and query ranges.  Adding a range involves finding its appropriate position in the list and merging overlapping ranges. Querying a range involves a binary search-like traversal to determine if the range is fully covered. Removing a range requires finding the overlapping ranges and adjusting their boundaries. This approach provides logarithmic time complexity for most operations due to the sorted nature of the data structure.  The space complexity is linear as it stores all the tracked ranges.

